		<article>
			<h1 class="storytitle"><a href="http://markos.gaivo.net/blog/?p=188" rel="bookmark">Bad marketing</a></h1>

			<div class="post-text">
				<p>If you own a company, you&#8217;re bound to be buried under an avalanche of various offers. I got one from HP today, trying to sell me a color laser printer with the following foldout (click for a bigger picture):</p>
<p><a href="http://www.marela.si/photos/7039/?original" title="Full size picture"><img src="http://static.marela.si/users0/markos/2/Dhkv4lp6mpC2gzRgcAzdfaaFSnc.jpg" alt="Print error on HP's foldout" /></a></p>
<p>Mistakes happen and printing ones are no exception. But sending such foldout to prospective buyers of printers?</p>
<p>Now that&#8217;s simply stupid.</p>
			</div>

